article.headline: Vermont 101, Quinnipiac 87
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. (AP) -- Joe Trapani and Mike Trimboli combined for 49 points to lead Vermont to a 101-87 win at Quinnipiac on Saturday. Trapani scored 25 points and Trimboli had 24 as the Catamounts (7-5) posted their second straight win. Chris Holm added 13 points and 11 rebounds for Vermont, which dominated inside with a 38-23 rebounding advantage. Quinnipiac's DeMario Anderson scored 17 of his team-high 20 points in the second half to keep his team close. Senior guard Adam Gonzalez added 17 points for the Bobcats (2-8), who lost their seventh straight game. It's the longest losing streak for Quinnipiac since the 1998-99 season. Trapani scored the first five points of the second half as Vermont opened up a 56-41 lead. But Quinnipiac got back into the game behind Anderson, who keyed the comeback with 13 points in a five-minute stretch midway through the second half, the last points coming on a 3-pointer to make it 71-65 with 10:37 remaining. Trimboli answered with nine points in the last nine minutes as the Catamounts pulled away. Catamounts shot 61 percent in the first half for a 51-43 lead at the break.
